column2: More green this year than normal.  Boat traffic heavy on day of reading- light wind.
Wind from se- temp. 82 degrees- partly cloudy.  Noted pieces of cut weed on surface.
Public perception also due to floating weed parts.  Had 2.5" rain in past 2-3 days.  Weed + parts of float down from big Chetac lake.
Overcast- temp. 76 degrees- humidity 86%- wind calm.  Little boat traffic.  Still weed floating down from big Chetac.
Public perception rated slightly.  Less floating and + cut weeds.  Excessive growth on bottom of moored sailboat-more than any year in past 6.
Area had 9.4" of rain in august.  No rain for past 7 days.  Light SE breeze + clear sky.
Green color is lighter now.  No floating weed parts.
Clear sky- light SW winds- temp. 68 degrees.  "green" is lighter and free of any floating weed bits.
Ice out April 29th. weather clear + sunny. waves near calm- ripples.
Overcast sky- temp. 67 degrees- waves 2-3". hazard + "slow-no wake" buoys have been placed. no milfoil reported or seen in 1995.
Air temp. 53 degrees- waves 1-2"- sky overcast- no sign of milfoil.
Floating weeds + grass from lake Chetac. air temp. 71 degrees- waves 1-2"- sky clear- wind from southwest 3-4 mph- boat traffic very light.
4.3" of rain yesterday. 5-6 mph S wind- waves 2-3". Sky clear + sunny. Temp (air) 78 degrees + humid.
Temp. 76 degrees- light SW wind- sky bright but overcast.
Temp. 73- no clouds- light winds from due south. no boat traffic.
Near calm. overcast about 80%. temp 67 degrees.
2" waves- air temp. 73 degrees- sky bright with light clouds about 30%.
Waves 2-3"- wind from SW 10 mph- temp. 79 degrees- no rain of note for 8-9 days.
2-3" waves- cloudy/bright- wind form south- very little boat traffic.
Cloudy- wind 10 mph from southwest. air temp 56 degrees. water color brownish green. no rain of note for 6-7 days.
Light mist with SE (1-2" waves) . no boat traffic. air temp. 53 degrees and overcast.
Wind less than 5 mph- ripples on water- air temp. 54 degrees- blue sky. Last reading for 1996.  Lake Level: Way below normal (lowest in 13 yrs.)
Waves 2-3" today. W/SW wind 10 mph. Bright sunshine. No boat traffic.
Little wind- 1" ripples- wind from northeast- very little boat traffic- 15-20% cloud cover- bright sun- hazard marker buoys are in place for the season.
50% cloud cover- wind from S @ 5 mph.- light bout traffic- waves 2"- air temp. 69 degrees.
Waves 1-3"- wind from SW- few boats on the lake.
Overcast sky (80% cloud) - light NW wind- very little boat traffic.
Had 6" rain in past 10 hours.- sky 90% overcast and wind 5-6 mph. from the southwest.
Calm no wind- air temp. 68 degrees- light boat traffic.
Water surface has millions of gnats on it- looks like algae bloom- but is not- first time ever noted.  Lake Level: well below normal
Heavy boat traffic (and jet skies) - very little rain for past 30 days- temp low 70's- wind w/southwest 3-5 mph.  Lake Level: well below normal
Temp. mid 70's- lake near calm- bright sunshine.
Had 1.9" of rain in past 24 hours. Northwest wind at 10 mph. Sky blue with 50% cloud cover.
Wind from the northwest at 8-10 mph.  Very little boat traffic.
Wind from the NW at 5-8- mph. sky 60% cloud cover.  Very few boats on the lake.
The sky is 100 % overcast- wind from the northeast is 6 mph. No boat traffic on lake.  Last report for 1997.  See you in the spring!
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
SAMPLED OVER DEEPEST PART NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
Data collected by BCABLA Voluteers on Birch Lake in 2017
low water - winter/fall drawdown in process
